The paper discusses motion planning for wheeled mobile robots, which is a topic within the field of robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes metrics for planning efficiency and path quality, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper compares different motion planning algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the algorithms involve learning or vision-based techniques.
